# Files to automatically delete from every extracted archive before the
# content is dispatched to its destination adapter.
#
# One exact filename per line. Only top-level members of the extracted
# directory are matched — subdirectory paths (containing '/') are not
# supported and will be skipped with a warning.
#
# Lines starting with '#' and blank lines are ignored.
# Trailing whitespace on each line is stripped automatically.
#
# The strip step runs in lib/extract.sh after 7z extracts all members and
# before the dispatch worker copies the result to its destination. This
# means stripped files are never sent to the adapter.
#
# The path to this file can be overridden with the EXTRACT_STRIP_LIST
# environment variable.

Vimm's Lair.txt
